Which of the following statements dealing with simple harmonic motion of a mass-spring system is TRUE?

choices.W: The acceleration is largest when the oscillating mass is instantaneously at rest.
choices.X: The larger the spring force constant the larger the period.
choices.Y: The period of the motion depends linearly on the amplitude of the motion.
choices.Z: The acceleration is larger when the oscillating mass has its greatest velocity.

answer: W- THE ACCELERATION IS LARGEST WHEN THE OSCILLATING MASS IS INSTANTANEOUSLY AT REST
